HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 356
By Howell
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Madison Wright of Polk
County, Tennessee delegate to the
Governmental Affairs Conference.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
citizens who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as community
leaders of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such exemplary individual is Madison Wright of Polk County, who
recently represented the State of Tennessee at the Governmental Affairs Conference (GAC),
March 2-6, 2025, in Washington, D.C., as a GAC "Crasher"; and
WHEREAS, the Crash the GAC program brings together rising industry leaders at the
Governmental Affairs Conference, and Ms. Wright was one of fifty-five credit union
professionals selected by Filene to "crash" the GAC; and
WHEREAS, Filene is an independent, consumer finance think tank dedicated to
scientific and thoughtful analysis of issues affecting consumer financial wellness, the future of
credit unions, and cooperative finance; and
WHEREAS, the Crash the GAC program has allowed up-and-coming members of the
credit union industry to experience the credit union movement first-hand since 2009; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Wright is the marketing representative/member experience specialist at
Copper Basin Federal Credit Union and an ambassador for the Polk County Chamber of
Commerce; and
WHEREAS, Madison Wright has demonstrated the utmost professionalism, ability, and
integrity as a credit union professional, winning the unbridled respect and admiration of her
colleagues and her customers alike; now, therefore,
